Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion shallot{1} into
small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).
Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips
then chop widthways into roughly 3cm pieces.

Pop the aubergine pieces onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{1%drizzle}
and season with @salt{pinch}, @pepper{pinch} and @North Indian style spice mix{1%pot}.
Toss to coat, then arrange in a single layer. Roast the aubergine until golden brown
and soft, ~{20-25%minutes}, turning halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a medium #saucepan{} on a medium
heat. When hot, add the shallot and cook, stirring frequently until tender,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Pour the @water for the rice{300} into another saucepan and bring to the boil.
When boiling, add @salt{1/4%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{150}, lower the heat
to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then
remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for
another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in
its own steam).

Add the @korma curry paste{50} and garlic to the shallot and cook, stirring
frequently for ~{1%minute}. Add the @tomato passata{1}, @red split lentils{100},
@water for the dal{350} and @vegetable stock paste{10}. Stir well and bring to a
boil. Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cook until the lentils are soft,
~{20-25%minutes}.

> Stir regularly to make sure it doesn't stick to the bottom of the pan and add a
> splash of water if it starts to get too thick.

Once the lentils are cooked, add the @baby spinach{40} a handful at a time,
stirring until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir through the roasted
aubergine and cook until everything is piping hot. Taste and season with @salt{}
and @pepper{} if necessary.

Once everything is ready, divide the rice between your plates. Top with the
aubergine dal and tuck in. Enjoy!